The Joker "tells" the magician what the 2 cards are.

SUBJECT: Magic with Wands

Spectator draws "X" on picture when picture is face down to mark a place on the spectator's body. Magician grabs an envelope and places the marker spectator used into it.  Magician crumples up envelope showing marker has vanished and spectator confirms it has reappeared in place he marked on his own body.

Then seals the marker in his envelope and puts the spectators envelope in the spectators pocket.  Magician crushes his envelope and spectator pulls his envelope out of his pocket to reveal the marker in his envelope.

DESCRIPTION: Handkerchief is removed several times from lunch bag and keeps reappearing.  All the while, a spectator hold another lunch bag tightly.  Magician finally places handkerchief into his lunchbag, rips lunch bag open to reveal handkerchief has vanished.  Spectator now opens theirs and pulls out handkerchief.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A silk is touched by a wand and clings to the wand. Sponge balls do likewise. Three cards selected from a deck of card are pulled out by the 'magnetic' wand.

SUBJECT: Double Paper Mysteries
TITLE: Puffing Rice in a Cone
DESCRIPTION: Magician takes single unpopped kernal of corn and tosses it into a lunch bag.  It pops.  He eats it and shows the bag empty.  He then pours lots of unpopped kernals into the bag.  Makes a magical gesture and dumps the bag into several cups, filling them up with popped popcorn.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A tip for a simplified version.

SUBJECT: Double Paper Mysteries
TITLE: The Two Way Paper Cone
DESCRIPTION: Handkerchief goes into a paper cone and when pulled out, has changed color.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A wand can be pushed into the spectator's body, swallowed almost completely, or pushed into a boy's head.

SUBJECT: Double Paper Mysteries
TITLE: Cut and Restored Handkerchief
DESCRIPTION: Handkerchief is cut with scissors.  Spectator holds lunch bag.  Both pieces of handkerchief are placed in lunch bag.  Thread and needle are placed in lunch bag.  Spectator reaches into lunch bag and pulls out needle and thread and the handkerchief is now attached to them and they have been sewn together.  All are placed back into bag.  Spectator holds bag.  Magical gesture.  Spectator opens bag and pulls out fully restored handkerchief
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A card is selected and torn. Spectator keeps one piece. Rest of the pieces are vanished. An egg is tapped by the wand, broken open, and the card is found inside, restored except for the missing piece.

SUBJECT: Double Paper Mysteries
TITLE: The Cards and Ribbons
DESCRIPTION: Spectator is handed lunch bag.  Spectator pulls out string and playing cards.  Spectator selects a card.  Magician selects a card.  Both sign their cards in different colored markers.  Magician places his card back in deck.  Spectator shuffles.  Spectator places his card back in deck.  Magician shuffles.  Magician places cards into bag.  Magician places string into bag, but holds onto 1 end.  Wriggles string and slowly pulls out string.  One card is connected to string.  It's the magicians card.  Spectator does the same and as he pulls out string, multiple cards are attached to string.  In fact, the whole deck is attached, EXCEPT his card.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A borrowed finger ring rises on command when placed on magician's wand.

SUBJECT: Double Paper Mysteries
TITLE: Royal Paper Cone
DESCRIPTION: How to make Royal paper cone.  Tissue paper is torn up into several pieces.  Pieces dropped into a cone.  Spectator reaches in and pulls out tissue paper chain.  Cone is shown empty and changes to Christmas tree, chain is wrapped around tree to decorate.  Spectator is handed colored markers.  Magician shows another empty cone where a blank paper is placed.  Magician closes cone.  Spectator draws imaginary picture of Santa in the air with colored markers.  Spectator pulls out paper and reveals a picture of Santa.  Magician turns cone into Santa's hat.  Magician pulls out wine glass and shows he's wearing Christmas socks.  He pulls 1 out of his pocket.  He ties 2 silks together.  He places silks in wine glass, has spectator place sock in cone.  Closes cone.  Spectator holds wine glass.  Magician counts to 3.  He opens cone to show sock is disappeared.  Spectator pulls on 1 of the silks to show sock in between both of the silks.  Magician turns cone into New Years party hat.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A match sized wand changes to a 5' wand and then a large wand.

SUBJECT: Double Paper Mysteries
TITLE: Century Card Vanishing Paper
DESCRIPTION: Magician pulls trick instructions out of an envelope along with a smaller envelope labled "For Emergency Use Only". Magician and spectator begin reading and following instructions including having spectator select card and wrap it in the instructions.  Magician waves hand over it.  It doesn't disappear.  Spectator gives magician driver's license which goes into the instructions with the card.  With another wave, both disappear.  Spectator spreads cards to reveal their card face up.  Emergency envelope is opened, spectator reaches in and pulls out their license.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A wand is vanished in a sheet of paper, to wind up hanging on the spectator's back (uses P-L wand)

SUBJECT: Double Paper Mysteries
TITLE: Acme Coin Vanishing Paper
DESCRIPTION: Coin is folded inside paper and vanishes.  Paper is folded again and coin returns.

SUBJECT: Double Paper Mysteries
TITLE: Modern Coin Vanishing Paper and Coin through the Saucer
BOOK_TITLE: Superba Paper Cone for Handkerchief Vanish
DESCRIPTION: Coin is selected and sign.  It is placed on paper and paper is folded to trap it.  Spectator uses tweezers to hold folded paper.  Canning jar is put together (Lid is placed on).  Paper is placed on top of canning jar.  Lighter fluid is sprayed on paper.  Paper is lit on fire.  Quarter drops through lid.  When jar is opened, quarter is found to be signed quarter.  Lid has no hole.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Paper is folded into a cone. A handkerchief is placed inside, and the top of the cone folded over. The handkerchief disappears.

SUBJECT: Magic with Coins
TITLE: Misers Dream
DESCRIPTION: Magician makes lots of coins appear and drops them in glass.  At end, makes dollar bill flower ball appear.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Paper is rolled into a cylinder and a silk is placed inside. Performer apparently removes silk and puts it in pocket, but it is still in the paper. Next, someone from backstage apparently removes the silk, but it is still there. Finally the silk disappears, to be found in a formerly empty glass.

SUBJECT: Magic with Coins
TITLE: Hand to Hand Flight of 4 coins
DESCRIPTION: Magician has 1 English penny and 4 quarters.  English penny goes in left hand, quarters in right.  1 at a time, the quarters pass.  With the last quarter, A spectator covers the English penny and 3 quarters and another spectator holds the magicians wrist.  He opens his hand to reveal the final quarter gone.  Spectator moves her hand to show English penny and all 4 quarters.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A paper is folded into a cone. Rice in a dish is shown, and a handful is dropped into the cone. Puffed rice is poured out of the cone!

SUBJECT: Magic with Coins
TITLE: Passe Coins and Glasses
DESCRIPTION: 3 coins get sealed in a canning jar. 1-by-1 they pass from the jar to a glass.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: How to construct and 11 ideas for using it.

SUBJECT: Magic with Coins
TITLE: The Passe Coins from Hand to Hand
DESCRIPTION: 1 at a time, 4 half dollars go from 1 hand to another. (shell)
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Vanish or produce small objects, like a torn playing card.

SUBJECT: Magic with Coins
TITLE: The Phantom Coin
DESCRIPTION: 2 coins go from 1 side of the table to another, then under a coin purse, then into a coin purse.  A Sharpie separates the coins in the middle of the table.  In the middle of the routine, the Sharpie vanishes. (shell)
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Vanish one or a few playing cards

SUBJECT: Magic with Coins
TITLE: Coin in the Magical Envelopes
DESCRIPTION: Spectator is handed a folded piece of paper. Borrowed, signed quarter is vanished. When spectator pulls out paper, it is now folded into 3 nested envelopes.  Spectator opens each envelope 1 by 1 and magician rips them up.  Envelope #3 contains the signed quarter.  Magician restores the envelopes and makes the quarter vanish again.  Once again, the envelopes are opened 1 by 1 and #3 contains the signed quarter.  Papers are restored to original paper once again.

SUBJECT: Cigarette Magic
TITLE: Push in Vanish
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Using a vanishing paper to have a coin penetrate the center of a glass saucer and land in a glass.

SUBJECT: Cigarette Magic
TITLE: Pivot Vanish
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Coins are produced from the air and thrown into a hat.

SUBJECT: Cigarette Magic
TITLE: Front and Back Hand Palm
BOOK_TITLE: Hand to Hand Flight of Four Coins
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A gold coin in the left hand attracts silver coins in the right hand one by one.

SUBJECT: Cigarette Magic
TITLE: Throwing Vanish
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Five coins are counted into a glass and held in one hand. The other hand holds an empty glass. One by one the coins pass from the one glass to the other.

SUBJECT: Cigarette Magic
TITLE: Pull-away Vanish
BOOK_TITLE: The Passe Coins from Hand to Hand
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Four coins pass one at a time from one hand to the other. (Uses shell)

SUBJECT: Cigarette Magic
TITLE: To Vanish Cigarette up the Nose and Produce from Ear
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: two quick tricks using a shell

SUBJECT: Cigarette Magic
TITLE: Swallowing a Cigarette
BOOK_TITLE: The Coin in the Magical Envelopes
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A borrowed, marked coin is wrapped in newspaper and handed to the spectator. Upon opening, however, the paper had changed into a paper envelope, with another envelope, with a third envelope inside. The marked coin is found inside. This is repeated. The envelopes are offered to the spectator as a souvenir, but change back to the normal newspaper.

SUBJECT: Cigarette Magic
TITLE: Multiplying Cigarette
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A cigarette is pushed into the hand and vanishes.

SUBJECT: Cigarette Magic
TITLE: Change Over Palm
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: a lighted cigarette is taken from the right hand by the left and vanishes, to be produced elsewhere.

SUBJECT: Cigarette Magic
TITLE: Burning Cig and silk Hank
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A cigarette is patted into the left fingers and the hand closed. The cigarette vanishes.

SUBJECT: Cigarette Magic
TITLE: Cig manip Routine
DESCRIPTION: Cigarette routine utilizing various sleight of hand moves.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Both sides of hand are shown empty, yet a cigarette can be produced.

SUBJECT: Cigarette Magic
TITLE: The Phantom Cig
DESCRIPTION: Invisible cigarette is rolled and put in lips.  When lit with match, it becomes visible.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A lighted cigarette is thrown into the left hand and found to vanish.

SUBJECT: Cigarette Magic
TITLE: The Vanishing Cigarette
DESCRIPTION: Lit cigarette vanishes then reappears. (pull)
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Cigarette held in closed hand, and is pushed in by right. When the hand is opened the cigarette has vanished.

SUBJECT: Cigarette Magic
TITLE: Vanishing Pencil
BOOK_TITLE: To Vanish a Cigarette Up the Nose
DESCRIPTION: Sharpie vanishes from hands (pull)

SUBJECT: Cigarette Magic
TITLE: The Dollar Bill in Cigarette
DESCRIPTION: Borrowed cigarrette vanishes while using it to make dollar disappear, appears behind ear.  Cigarette actually makes dollar vanish.  Cigarette is ripped in half (carefully) to reveal the dollar inside of it.

SUBJECT: Cigarette Magic
TITLE: Catching Cigarettes in the Air
DESCRIPTION: Different colored suckers are plucked out of thin air and placed into a bag.  After several colors are plucked out of the air and placed into the bag, real fruit is dumped out of the bag.

SUBJECT: Cigarette Magic
TITLE: Odd Cigarette Vanish
BOOK_TITLE: Vanish and Production by Paul Fox
DESCRIPTION: Several toy cat mice are placed into lunch bag from pet store shopping bag.  Spectator reaches inside and pulls out 1 can of Fancy Feast cat food.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Cigarette vanishes from left hand. Both hands shown empty, cigarette is found behind left hand.

SUBJECT: Cigarette Magic
TITLE: Cardini's Floating Cigarette
DESCRIPTION: Cigarette floats inside of clear tube with top on it.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A second cigarette is produced from one.

SUBJECT: Cigarette Magic
TITLE: Lighted Cigarette from Box
DESCRIPTION: Lit cigarette is produced from borrowed pack of cigarettes
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Both hands are shown empty, yet a cigarette can be produced.

SUBJECT: Sleight of Hand with Cards
TITLE: Front and Back Hand Palming
BOOK_TITLE: The Burning Cigarette and Silk Handkerchief
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A lit cigarette is placed in left hand and turns into a silk.

SUBJECT: Sleight of Hand with Cards
TITLE: Production of Cards One at a Time From Back of Hand
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: An imaginary cigarette is placed in the mouth. A box of matches is produced, and match lit and brought to the mouth. Suddenly a real cigarette appears which is lit.

SUBJECT: Sleight of Hand with Cards
TITLE: Production from Front of Hand
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A lit cigarette is placed in the hand and vanishes.

SUBJECT: Sleight of Hand with Cards
TITLE: To Vanish Cards One at a Time and Reproduce Them
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: As above but with pencil Cigarette

SUBJECT: Sleight of Hand with Cards
TITLE: Flash Card Production
BOOK_TITLE: The Dollar Bill in the Cigarette
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A bill is borrowed and the number noted. A cigarette is selected and placed in the mouth. The bill is made to vanish and appears inside the cigarette.

SUBJECT: Sleight of Hand with Cards
TITLE: Color Changes with Cards
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A box is shown with cigarettes in it. Cigarettes are taken one at a time from the box and placed in another. The second box is then shown to be empty!

SUBJECT: Sleight of Hand with Cards
TITLE: Top Card Change
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A borrowed cigarette is placed in a tube. A hoop is passed over the tube, yet the cigarette rises and falls inside.

SUBJECT: Sleight of Hand with Cards
TITLE: Modern Card Change
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A lit cigarette is removed from a case.

SUBJECT: Sleight of Hand with Cards
TITLE: Card Change Performance
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Cards are produced although empty hand is shown front and back.

SUBJECT: Sleight of Hand with Cards
TITLE: Second Dealing
BOOK_TITLE: Production of Cards One at a Time from Back of Hand.

SUBJECT: Sleight of Hand with Cards
TITLE: The Ribbon Drop
BOOK_TITLE: Production of Cards One at a Time from Front of Hand.

SUBJECT: Sleight of Hand with Cards
TITLE: The Cascade
BOOK_TITLE: To Vanish Cards One a Time and Reproduce Them.

SUBJECT: Sleight of Hand with Cards
TITLE: Production of Cards from Mouth
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A paper 'tambourine' is created and is obviously empty, the performer plunges his hand through and produces a card fan.

SUBJECT: Sleight of Hand with Cards
TITLE: One-Handed Cut
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: the phantom pip, back hand color change, open finger color change, slap change, push up color change, thumb steal color change, double card change, slip up color change, top card change (4 methods), modern card change, single hand card change.

SUBJECT: Selected Card Mysteries
TITLE: Any Name Called For
DESCRIPTION: Spectator deals off 2 even piles of cards (any number of cards they wish).  They mix up their pile and look at bottom card.  The other spectator replaces their cards.  Spectator 1 spells a name of their choosing.  The card they deal to is the card they remembered.

SUBJECT: Selected Card Mysteries
TITLE: The 10 Card Color Change
DESCRIPTION: Variation of Follow the Leader.  Separate 10 black cards from 10 red cards.  No matter where the "Leader" card is, the colors always follow.

SUBJECT: Selected Card Mysteries
TITLE: Double Detection
DESCRIPTION: 2 spectators take half the deck each and cut their decks behind their backs and flip them face-to-face.  When both halves are brought out, both spectators have cut right to all 4 Aces.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: The ribbon drop, the cascade, production of cards from the mouth, cascade production from boy's nose, the one handed cut Sleight, Manipulation

SUBJECT: Selected Card Mysteries
TITLE: A Clever Card Discovery & Baker Telephone Mystery
DESCRIPTION: Spectator 1 shuffles half the deck, spectator 2 shuffles the other half.  Spectator 1 looks at bottom card (must be number card) and deals that many cards face down on table.  The rest of the cards go on top of the cards dealt on table.  Spectator 2 repeats the process with their cards.  Magician "pretends" to call spectator 1 and gets them to pick up their half deck of cards and turn them face up.  He instructs them to call out the card they see and deal it to the table and continue the process.  He tells them he will try to find the card they are thinking of "by the tone of their voice".  Spectator 2 tries to not look directly at their card, but the magician locates it anyway.

SUBJECT: Selected Card Mysteries
TITLE: McCaffery Variaion of the Telephone Mystery
DESCRIPTION: Spectator 1 looks at bottom number card and hands spectator 2 that many cards.  Spectator 2 shuffles those cards, looks at top card, puts it back.  The rest of the deck is now dropped on top of the selected card and pile.  Magician is still able to locate the card.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A packet of cards is taken by the spectator, and the same number of cards is then counted off the remainder of the deck. This bottom card is memorized. Performer picks up deck, and spells of three or more names. The spectator places his stack of cards back and does the same, resulting in finding his selected card.

SUBJECT: Selected Card Mysteries
TITLE: Prophetic Card Discovery
DESCRIPTION: Spectator selects card and magician is able to know it.  Magician then helps spectator locate his own card by doing a rocket "count down" 4 times.  If any "count downs" are "scrubbed", the "scrubbed" launches are added and that many cards are dealt down to reveal the spectator's card.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Ten black cards and ten red cards are counted to the table. The red cards are placed on the black cards face up and shown. The black cards are now dealt and then the red cards. Blacks now change to red, and red to black. The cards then change to suit the way they are dealt.

SUBJECT: Selected Card Mysteries
TITLE: The Conjurors Touch
DESCRIPTION: Spectator selects any card from deck and places it into card box. Rest of deck goes into magician's pocket. Magician pulls out a card and asks for suit, card matches suit.  Magician reaches in and pulls out 2 more cards that matches value when added to suit card. (2 peeks taught)
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Spectator cuts deck behind his back and reverses the bottom packet. The performer can name the two facing cards.

SUBJECT: Selected Card Mysteries
TITLE: A Mysterious Discovery
DESCRIPTION: Spectator 1 thinks of a number and pulls off that many cards from the bottom of the deck and mixes them and hands 1 to spectator 2. Spectator 2 memorizes it and places it on top of the rest of the deck and spectator 1 places the rest of her cards on top of the card.  The deck gets cut.  Magician is unable to locate cards so takes them all and mixes them face down into a pile.  Uses Spectator 1 to locate a card with the value equal to the number she selected.  Uses spectator 2's finger to locate the card she memorized.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A deck is shuffled and the top card remembered. Cards are removed from the bottom, the same value as the memorized card, and placed on top. The cards are then cut. The performer can find the selected card.

SUBJECT: Selected Card Mysteries
TITLE: Marvello
DESCRIPTION: Deck is shuffled and split in half.  half the deck is split in half again and each quarter of the deck is handed to 2 different spectators.  Each spectator thinks of a card in their pack.  They also think of the number position that card is at.  Both packs get turned upside down.  Magician slowly counts down to that position and pulls out the card and partially places it into the rest of the deck (with each quarter packet).  Both cards are clearly seen partially in the half deck (upside down).  Spectator 2 now selects a 3rd card which gets placed face up in the 2 packs that the selected cards originally came from and that gets set aside.  Both of the selected cards get squared into the half deck very slowly.  Magician invisibly moves cards from half deck to packet deck.  New selected card that was placed face up is between 2 cards.  Half deck is turned face up and spread.  The selected cards have vanished.  The 2 cards surrounding new card are flipped face up to show they are selected cards.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Over the phone, the spectator is asked to shuffle the deck and look at the bottom card. This same value of cards is now dealt from the top of the deck to the bottom, and performer can now find the card.

SUBJECT: Rising Cards
TITLE: Cardini's Rising Cards
BOOK_TITLE: McCaffrey's Variation of the Telephone Mystery
DESCRIPTION: Deck rises out of card case.  Multiple cards are selected, memorized, and returned to deck.  One at a time, the cards rise out of the deck.

SUBJECT: Rising Cards
TITLE: Rising Deck from Card Case
DESCRIPTION: Deck rises out of card case.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A prediction is written on a paper. A spectator selects three cards as instructed, and cards are added to each pile to make the value of the pile equal ten. The cards are then added together, and that number of cards are counted down in the remaining deck. The performer has predicted the found card.

SUBJECT: Rising Cards
TITLE: Pack Full of Pep
DESCRIPTION: Revised version of deck rising from case
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A deck is shuffled and a card removed. The deck is placed in the performer's pocket. The suit of the card is named, and immediately a card of the same suit is removed from the deck. The number is named, and immediately a card of the same value is removed.

SUBJECT: Rising Cards
TITLE: The Rising Cards and Card Case
DESCRIPTION: Several cards are selected and one by one, they rise from the deck. The last card rises from magicians coat pocket.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Deck of cards spread in a row. Spectator picks up 1-10 cards and moves them to the other end, remembering one of the cards. Magician spreads cards back out and moves spectator's wrist over the cards. He stops and the selected card number is the same value as the number of cards move. He moves and stops again, this time at the selected card

SUBJECT: Rising Cards
TITLE: Rising Card from Pocket
DESCRIPTION: Card rises from pocket (performance in "The Rising Cards and Card Case")
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Two spectators think of numbers and as the cards are dealt, they remember the card at the selected number. The numbers are now announced, and the performer counts out the cards and places the selections aside. Two random cards are then removed and placed in an envelope. The random cards change places with the selected cards.

SUBJECT: Rising Cards
TITLE: Rising Cards from Glass Goblet
DESCRIPTION: 4 cards selected and returned to deck and shuffled.  Placed in clear goblet.  Magician uses "imp" to tell him what the cards are and to cause the cards to rise out of the glass one by one. Cards are handed out for examination afterwards

SUBJECT: Rising Cards
TITLE: Goblet Variations
DESCRIPTION: Variations on rising cards from a goblet
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Five cards are selected and returned to the deck. They rise one at a time with the last two rising at once. The deck may now be examined.

SUBJECT: Rising Cards
TITLE: Howard Thurston Rising Cards
DESCRIPTION: Cards are shuffled, a card is freely selected and signed, and cards are passed out 2 more times.  Cards are replaced into the deck and magically rise one by one to the magician's hand.  The cards (including deck) can be handed out before and after.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: The entire deck rises from the case.

SUBJECT: Rising Cards
TITLE: Superba Rising Cards & Thurston's Floating Card
DESCRIPTION: 3 cards selected from card deck are placed back into the deck and the deck placed into goblet.  Cards rise out of deck to magician's hands one by one.

SUBJECT: Rising Cards
TITLE: De Kolta Card Fountain
BOOK_TITLE: The Rising Cards and Card Case
DESCRIPTION: Spectator chooses which of 2 decks is the "magic" deck.  Magician does not touch that deck.  Magician uses other deck to have cards selected.  One by one, the cards rise out of the deck that has never been touched.  The last card is found to be showing on the bottom of the deck.  Instead of having it rise, the magician causes the rest of the deck to jump from the goblet like a fountain, leaving only the last card.  Both goblet and cards can be handed out.  (uses assistant and special setup)
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Card are cut and three cards are selected from one half and placed in the other. The entire deck is now placed in the case and the three cards rise one by one.

SUBJECT: Rising Cards
TITLE: Harry Stork Card Fountain
DESCRIPTION: Another variation of De Kolta Card Fountain
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A card is selected and returned to the deck. A card is poorly transferred to the pants pocket, and when questioned, the performer points to his shirt pocket, where the Ace of Diamonds rises. The spectator says this is not the card, but on a second look, it is the spectator's card.

SUBJECT: Rising Cards
TITLE: Jean Hugard's Card Fountain
DESCRIPTION: Another variation of De Kolta Card Fountain
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Three cards are selected and put back in the deck. The deck is put in a glass, and a hoop passed to show no attachments. Yet the cards rise from the deck. The cards and glass can be examined.

SUBJECT: Rising Cards
TITLE: Tommy Dowd's Rising Cards
DESCRIPTION: 3 cards are selected and placed back into the deck. Deck in placed inside glass with another glass placed on top of it.  Handkerchief is placed over top and when handkerchief is removed, 1 of the selected cards is shown to have risen from the deck.  The top glass is placed back on top and a 2nd selected card is openly seen to rise inside the glasses.  The deck is handed to the 3rd spectator to locate his card and offered to spectator to have him move his card to a different location in the deck.  The deck is placed in the card box and the box in the glasses.  The card openly rises.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Four cards are named. Deck is shuffled and placed in a goblet. The four cards one at a time soar up to the performer's hand, high above the glass. The cards are thrown to the audience.

SUBJECT: Egg Magic
TITLE: Humpty Dumpty Outdone
DESCRIPTION: Egg is signed and placed into folded handkerchief.  Spectator can feel egg in handkerchief.  Spectator cracks egg in handkerchief.  Magician waves lighter under handkerchief.  Spectator reaches in handkerchief and pulls out his signed egg fully restored and "cooked" (actually hard boiled).
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Selected cards rise from the deck in a glass to the performer's hand high above.

SUBJECT: Egg Magic
TITLE: Tarbell's Unbreakable Egg
DESCRIPTION: An egg is taken and placed in a folded handkerchief.  Spectator can feel the egg.  Spectator cracks egg.  Magician restores egg.  Spectator cracks it to show it's just a regular raw egg.  (Variation of Humpty Dumpty Outdone)(Uses Devil's handkerchief)
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: As above, but the last card actually floats in the air, and can be waved all around, finally to rise to the hand.

SUBJECT: Egg Magic
TITLE: The Egg Bag
DESCRIPTION: Egg mysteriously appears and vanishes from bag.  Ends with Onion appearing in bag.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Three cards are selected and returned to the deck which is placed in a goblet. All the cards begin to fly out except the three chosen cards.

SUBJECT: Egg Magic
TITLE: Fool-zum Egg Bag Routine
DESCRIPTION: A ring is shown that it is too small to fit around an egg.  A bag is forced through the ring, and when the spectator reaches into the bag, they pull out an egg.  The egg goes from bag to pocket and back with the bag even vanishing.  At the end, the wooden egg turns to a real egg that is cracked open.

SUBJECT: Billiard Ball Manipulation
TITLE: The Routine with Billiard Balls
DESCRIPTION: Billiard balls appear, disappear, and multiply trhoughout a full routine.

SUBJECT: Billiard Ball Manipulation
TITLE: Dan's Bonus Routine
DESCRIPTION: How to do Multiplying Billiard Balls without loads
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Cards are selected and returned to the deck. The deck is placed in a glass, with another glass placed on top. The cards rise into the other glass, and may be removed by spectator.

SUBJECT: Billiard Ball Manipulation
TITLE: Rainbow Billiard Balls
DESCRIPTION: Billiard balls multiply, but in multiplying, change color.  At the end, 1 ball changes to many different color silks (silk fountain)

SUBJECT: Billiard Ball Manipulation
TITLE: A Mysterious Ball Transposition
DESCRIPTION: 2 different colored plastic easter eggs are shown.  Something valuable from the audience is placed into each of them and placed into folded handkerchiefs.  In full view, the eggs switch places and are opened to show that the items are in the eggs as well.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Egg and handkerchief are examined. Egg is dropped into handkerchief, and then broken by the spectator. Spectator reaches in to remove egg, and it is whole.

SUBJECT: Billiard Ball Manipulation
TITLE: A Mysterious Ball Transposition (Disco Version)
DESCRIPTION: Magic 8-Ball and Disco Ball of similar size are both placed in different handkerchiefs and both swap places.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: As above, uses a double handkerchief.

SUBJECT: Sleight of hand with Coins
TITLE: Palming/Vanishing
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Discusses some brief history. Provides a routine in which an egg transports between a handkerchief and an egg bag in mysterious ways. Describes how to make a Tarbell Style egg bag and devil's handkerchief'.

SUBJECT: Sleight of hand with Coins
TITLE: Front Flat Palm (Classic Palm)
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Uses silken egg bag and an ungimmicked duplicate. Bag is pushed through metal ring, egg is produced. At the end, the bag turns into an egg, which is cracked open into a glass.

SUBJECT: Sleight of hand with Coins
TITLE: Front Edge Palm (Classic Edge Grip)
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Billiard balls (shell) multiply and vanish in the hand to the patter of a story of Adam and Eve.

SUBJECT: Sleight of hand with Coins
TITLE: Invisible Thumb Palm (Downs Palm)
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Red white green and yellow balls appear and change color in this routine. (4 colored balls, one shell)

SUBJECT: Sleight of hand with Coins
TITLE: Finger Palm
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Green ball wrapped in green handkerchief and placed in glass changes places with red ball wrapped in red handkerchief placed in another glass. (2 color balls, one shell)

SUBJECT: Sleight of hand with Coins
TITLE: Front Finger Palm
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Sleeves are rolled up, yet a rolled up handkerchief vanishes, both sides of hands being shown empty. The silk reappears.

SUBJECT: Sleight of hand with Coins
TITLE: Back Finger Palm
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Folded newspaper and soup plate are placed on a chair. Two silks are vanished, and appear under the soup plate.

SUBJECT: Sleight of hand with Coins
TITLE: Front to Back Transfer
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Two empty plates are shown and put together mouth to mouth. Two silks are vanished and found between the plates.

SUBJECT: Sleight of hand with Coins
TITLE: Front Finger Clip

SUBJECT: Sleight of hand with Coins
TITLE: Back Finger Clip
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A silk handkerchief tucked into the hand turns into a billiard ball.

SUBJECT: Sleight of hand with Coins

BOOK_TITLE: Christopher's Three Knots in a Rope
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Three knots appear in a six foot rope. One is blown and vanishes, the second is untied to show it is real, the third is visibly pulled off the rope and thrown to the audience.

SUBJECT: Sleight of hand with Coins
TITLE: Two Finger Balance
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A knot is tied in the end of a rope and held under the foot. Suddenly the knot jumps to the top of the rope.

SUBJECT: Sleight of hand with Coins
TITLE: Thumb-Fingertip Horizontal Hold
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A finger ring is borrowed, wrapped in a handkerchief and handed to a spectator to hold. A rope is held between the foot and the hand, and the handkerchief is waved at the rope. The ring appears knotted in the center of the rope.

SUBJECT: Sleight of hand with Coins
TITLE: Ramsey Subtlety
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A length of thread is produced and a knot is magically tied, but when other can't see it, it changes instantly to a rope.

SUBJECT: Sleight of hand with Coins
TITLE: Thumb-Fingertip Vertical Hold
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: follow up to Thread to Rope mystery. Rope unties itself.

SUBJECT: Sleight of hand with Coins
TITLE: Production Clip
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Lighted cigarette is placed into left fist. It turns into a 5 foot rope.

SUBJECT: Sleight of hand with Coins
TITLE: Pinch Clip
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A knot tied in a rope disappears with a simple pass of the hand.

SUBJECT: Sleight of hand with Coins
TITLE: Flat Finger Position
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Rope is coiled and placed on table; when pulled up, it is filled with knots. It is placed on the table again, and the knots vanish.

SUBJECT: Sleight of hand with Coins
TITLE: Fist Horizontal and Fist Vertical Holds

SUBJECT: Sleight of hand with Coins
TITLE: Front Thumb Palm Vanish
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A system of interlaced knots are untied even though the ends are held by a spectator. Rope

SUBJECT: Sleight of hand with Coins
TITLE: Top Pocket Vanish
BOOK_TITLE: Hocus Pocus Cut and Restored Rope
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Two ends are tied, and the loop shown. It is double coiled and cut, and the knot is cut away. Rope is tied again. The knot disappears, healing the rope.

SUBJECT: Sleight of hand with Coins
TITLE: Front Flat Palm Vanish
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A false knot that does not have to be slid off.

SUBJECT: Sleight of hand with Coins
TITLE: Front Finger Palm Vanish
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Rope is brought up in a loop and cut, both pieces being shown. The rope is restored.

SUBJECT: Sleight of hand with Coins
TITLE: Finger Palm Vanish
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A rope is cut into four pieces and restored.

SUBJECT: Sleight of hand with Coins
TITLE: Lift Up Vanish
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: a very short suggestion for a full routine.

SUBJECT: Sleight of hand with Coins
TITLE: Le Tourniquet Vanish (French Drop)
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Floating pips in the dark form the selected card.

SUBJECT: Sleight of hand with Coins
TITLE: Le Paul's Improved "French" Vanish
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: a forced word from a book revealed.

SUBJECT: Sleight of hand with Coins
TITLE: Tarbell's "Nip-Away" Coin Vanish
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A side of a die is selected and placed face up by the spectator, then placed into a bag. The magician opens the bag, removes the die, and divulges the number.

SUBJECT: Sleight of hand with Coins
TITLE: The Superba Coin Vanish
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Spectator selects page in weekly newspaper and notes top line. Magician takes paper, turns to proper page, and reads the selection.

SUBJECT: Sleight of hand with Coins
TITLE: The Direct Coin Vanish
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Ash tray held behind back; spectator places item there, concentrates on it, and removes it. Magician can reveal item.

SUBJECT: Sleight of hand with Coins
TITLE: Pick-Up Vanish
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: lights appear from nowhere and move about in darkened room.

SUBJECT: Sleight of hand with Coins
TITLE: Ditching (To get rid of coin after vanishing it in hand)

SUBJECT: Handkerchief Magic
TITLE: The Handkerchief Ball
DESCRIPTION: A ping pong ball utility device to vanish and appear silks
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Magician wraps self in blanket to mimic mummy. Assistant protests and show magician how to do it. A man from audience joins and the three argue. Suddenly the man removes his costume and is found to be the assistant. The blanket is opened and a girl appears!

SUBJECT: Handkerchief Magic
TITLE: Soup Plate and Handkerchiefs
DESCRIPTION: 3 different color silks are caused to vanish and then all reappear together.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Hindu magician ties girl in sack and places screen around her. After moving around a bit, the sack is opened and found to be the magician, the Hindu costume is removed and found to be the girl.

SUBJECT: Handkerchief Magic
TITLE: Two Soup Plates and Handkerchiefs
DESCRIPTION: 2 styrofoam plates are stapled together by the spectator to form a frisbee. 4 different color silks are selected. 2 are given to the magician, 2 are kept by spectator. 1 of spectator's silks goes back into bowl it came out of.  All other silk's are gotten rid of.  Magician causes silk to disappear.  Spectator picks up "frisbee" and tears it to find silk.

SUBJECT: Handkerchief Magic
TITLE: Twentieth Century Silks
DESCRIPTION: 1 pair of socks is placed in a goblet, another pair is placed in a lunch bag.  Sock is pulled from lunch bag, but no longer a pair, socks are pulled from goblet and other sock from lunch bag is shown pinned between this pair.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Three large playing cards are held flat and carried one at a time to center of stage. A real 'queen' appeared from within them!

SUBJECT: Handkerchief Magic
TITLE: Handkerchief to Billard Ball
DESCRIPTION: Handkerchief appears and when rolled into your hand, becomes a billiard ball.

SUBJECT: Handkerchief Magic
TITLE: The Elusive Rainbow
DESCRIPTION: Black and white silks are tied together, knot is placed in magician's mouth, when pulled out, several different colored silks come out all tied together.

SUBJECT: Handkerchief Magic
TITLE: Spot the Red
DESCRIPTION: Spectator places something valuable into plastic easter egg, Silk is pulled out and covers egg.  Egg disappears.  Another silk is brought out and both are tied together.  Knot is placed in magician's mouth, and 3rd (different color silk this time) is brought out and poked into magician's hand.  It turns into plastic egg.  Silk's are pulled out of magician's mouth and yellow silk is found to be tied between them.  Egg is vanished again.  Egg is found to be in mouth.  Egg is dumped out and spectator confirms item is theirs.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: strange card prediction, chosen by rolling a die

SUBJECT: Rope Magic
TITLE: Christopher's Three Knots in a Rope
DESCRIPTION: Magician ties 3 knots into a rope at once then magically makes 2 of them disappear.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: nail writer, through envelope, carbon paper

SUBJECT: Rope Magic
TITLE: Christopher's Jumping Knot
DESCRIPTION: Magician makes a knot at the bottom of the rope jump to the top
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: magician blindfolded, three spectators choose cards two exchange cards, magicican knows who and the cards, marked stacked deck

SUBJECT: Rope Magic
TITLE: Tannen's Ring, Knot and Rope
DESCRIPTION: A ring is placed into a folded handkerchief and held by the spectator that owns the ring.  Magician grabs one corner of handkerchief, sets up a rope for 1-handed knot.  As he ties 1-handed knot, he whips handkerchief towards rope and when knot forms, ring is found to be tied in rope.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: clock time duplication, then drawn card is found by medium

SUBJECT: Rope Magic
TITLE: A Rope Routine
DESCRIPTION: Routine utilizing "Christopher's Thread to Rope", "Self-Untying Rope", "The Phantom Knot", "Hindu Knots", "'Hocus Pocus' Cut and Restored Rope", and "Ted Collins' Panama Rope Mystery

SUBJECT: Rope Magic
TITLE: Christopher's Thread to Rope
DESCRIPTION: Rope appears from nowhere

SUBJECT: Rope Magic
TITLE: Self-Untying Rope
DESCRIPTION: Rope moves like snake to untie itself

SUBJECT: Rope Magic
TITLE: The Phantom Knot
DESCRIPTION: Knot is tied but disappears instantly

SUBJECT: Rope Magic
TITLE: Hindu Knots
DESCRIPTION: Several knots instantly appear in the rope and are instantly untied

SUBJECT: Rope Magic
TITLE: Hocus Pocus Cut and Restored Rope
DESCRIPTION: Rope is cut to make 2 pieces of rope.  They are tied together.  1 loop is tied at each end of the new "long" rope.  Rope is cut at knots to free loops.  Rope now has 3 knots on it.  It is wrapped around magician's hand.  When rope is unwrapped, knots have vanished.

SUBJECT: Rope Magic
TITLE: Ted Collins' Panama Rope Mystery
BOOK_TITLE: Value of an Opening, Psychology of Laughter
DESCRIPTION: Rope is cut to make 2 pieces of rope.  They are tied together.  1 loop is tied at each end of the new "long" rope.  Rope is cut at knots to free loops.  Rope now has 3 knots on it.  It is wrapped around magician's hand.  When rope is unwrapped, knots have vanished.

SUBJECT: Rope Magic
TITLE: Christopher's Cigarette to Rope
DESCRIPTION: Lit cigarette to rope;  Another lit cigarette to rope; Card box turns to cigarette pack. Rope is pulled out. Cigarette pack is turned back to card box and card deck is pulled out and a card is chosen.  Cards are placed back into box and when shaken, a silk is pulled out of box and cards have vanished.

SUBJECT: Rope Magic
TITLE: Tarbell's Triple Chefalo Knot
BOOK_TITLE: Magic Plots and Play Plots, Alike
DESCRIPTION: How to tie a knot that's not a knot (Dealing with difficulties and getting out of them)

SUBJECT: Rope Magic
TITLE: Another Rope Routine (Magician's Cut and Restored Rope, Perplexo Cut and Restored Rope, Himber's Rope Mystery, A Novel Knot Steal)
DESCRIPTION: Magician cuts rope, ties knot and restores rope. Rope is cut again and instantly restored. Rope is cut, yet again, and again restored. Knot is tied in center of rope and THEN cut, and rope is again restored.

SUBJECT: Ghostlite Mysteries
TITLE: Ghostlight Mysteries Routine Performance
BOOK_TITLE: Magic Should Never Offend or Embarrass
DESCRIPTION: Spectator selects a children toy block with a letter on it at random. They remember that letter.  Another spectator, without knowing the letter selected, eliminates blocks down to 1.  It is the 1 the spectator selected and it matches a newspaper clipping about a boy that died years ago whose name begins with the same letter. Spectator selects an item that was a posession of someone from long ago. Spectator writes name of someone they know on slate. From deck of cards, they select a card without looking at it and place it in an envelope.  The other items of posession go in the bag with the toy blocks. The selected item goes into a pocket. Magician and spectator place hands on the table. Spectator turns off lamp, making theater go dark. In the dark, 3 glowing diamonds appear floating in air. The light is turned back on and the random card is shown to be the 3 of diamonds. The name is erased from the slate. The light is turned back off. A glowing spider appears and crawls on spectator. Chalk glows and is seen to write on slate by itself. Light goes back on. A message is now on the slate saying, "Careful, I'm watching - "name of person spectator thought of and erased"".  Lights are turned back off and ghostly figure appears floating.  Lights are turned back on. Item from pocket is now on picture. Lights go back out and glowing work appears.  Scary glowing face appears. Lights are turned back on. Everything is gone.

SUBJECT: Ghostlite Mysteries
TITLE: Ghostlight Mysteries Chair Performance
DESCRIPTION: Magician sits in chair, spectators hold magician's wrists tightly. Lights go out. Glowing face appears and vanishes. Light comes back on. Spectators are still holding magician's wrists. This time they also hold his knees.

SUBJECT: Ghostlite Mysteries
TITLE: Ghostlight Mysteries Routine Performance (Night-vision)
DESCRIPTION: A night-vision view of the full routine performance and chair performance.

SUBJECT: Ghostlite Mysteries
TITLE: Introduction and Props
DESCRIPTION: Props and routine explanation of both performances.

SUBJECT: Illusions
TITLE: The Mystery of King Tut #1
DESCRIPTION: 3 paintings are set up in a triangle. Woman appears from center of them.  When trick is repeated, this time, magician appears out of triangle and assistant is magician.

SUBJECT: Illusions
TITLE: Who and Which #2
DESCRIPTION: $20 is clipped to a Star Wand in center of stage. Spectator is blindfolded and wrapped in cloth and informed that if they can knock over wand, they get $20. As they wobble toward the wand, magician cheats and picks up wand, guiding spectator in the wrong direction.  After a little bit, spectator appears in back of audience, comes to front and grabs $20. Wrapped up spectator is unwrapped to reveal surprise assistant.

SUBJECT: Illusions
TITLE: Three Kings and a Queen #3
DESCRIPTION: Circular time device is wheeled onto stage. There is a bodybag connected to it. Magician gets into full hazard suit. Assistant gets into safety vest. Assistant gets into bodybag and sticks hands out of bag. Magician operates time device. Something appears to go wrong, Magician removes hazard gear to reveal he is now assistant.  Bodybag is opened to reveal assistant is now magician.

SUBJECT: Mental Magic
TITLE: The Optical Force
DESCRIPTION: 4 cards are chosen at random (1 by magician, 3 by spectators). All cards are the exact same (all 5's).

SUBJECT: Mental Magic
TITLE: Demon Digits
DESCRIPTION: 3 digits are thought of by the spectator (all different digits). The numbers are reversed, then both numbers are subtracted.  Total is written down.  Magician uses playing cards to reveal all 3 digits of the total.

SUBJECT: Mental Magic
TITLE: Ultra Die
DESCRIPTION: Magician draws something on business card and folds business card and hands it to spectator to keep safe. 6 cards are randomly selected from shuffled deck. The 6 cards are placed face down in random places in the deck. A die is rolled and the number that comes up on the die is the face down card removed for the prediction. It matches what he wrote in the beginning.

SUBJECT: Mental Magic
TITLE: The Folded Prophecy
DESCRIPTION: Greeting card inside envelope is passed around the audience. When it randomly stops, audience member who has it comes up. The card is pulled out and it has the letter of the persons middle name.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Paper torn into 8 pieces and placed in two piles. Spectator selects one pile, magician draws crosses on each of the other papers. These are burnt. Spectator's papers now have crosses.

SUBJECT: Mental Magic
TITLE: Liars Convention
DESCRIPTION: After cutting the cards several times, the top 3 cards are pulled off the deck by 3 spectators. The spectators decide which card to show to the audience. 1 spectator shows their card, the other 2 switch their cards. All 3 make sure their cards are face down.  The magician then attempts to divise who showed the card via vocal inflection. The magician then proceeds to divine the exact card.  Deck is cut again. Each spectator takes a new card. Again 1 spectator shows a card. Again, the magician is able to divine who showed and what the card is.  Trick is repeated a 3rd time.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Palm is shown empty, cardboard is placed on top and two crosses are marked on the cardboard and erased. When removed, the crosses have transferred to the palm.

SUBJECT: Mental Magic
TITLE: Clocks and Cards
DESCRIPTION: Spectator draws hands on an analog clock representing the time they were born. Assistant receives your watch and uses dials to turn hands to spectator's birth time. A playing card is drawn in under the clock. The assistant is handed a shuffled deck of cards.  Assistant removes 1 card...  It matches drawn card.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A mark made on a sugar lump transfers to a plate.

SUBJECT: Mental Magic
TITLE: Roughing It
DESCRIPTION: 5 cards are removed from deck and the deck is turned face up. Spectator remembers 1 of the 5 cards and mixes the packet up.  Spectator then places the 5 face down cards into the face up deck anywhere randomly.  Behind his back, magician locates the face down cards and flips 4 of them over leaving only 1 face down - the spectator's thought of card.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A coin is produced from a paper match book

SUBJECT: Routining a Magic Show
TITLE: Introduction
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Matches in book are counted. One is removed and burnt. It is found back in the book, but burnt!

SUBJECT: Routining a Magic Show
TITLE: The Secret to a Better Routine
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A sort of multiplying match sticks routine

SUBJECT: Routining a Magic Show
TITLE: Scripting
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A match penetrates the metal of a safety pin

SUBJECT: Routining a Magic Show
TITLE: Choosing Material
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Bar bet to have a match stand on its edge

SUBJECT: Routining a Magic Show
TITLE: Putting it in Order
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Match rises and falls at will in pop bottle of water

SUBJECT: Routining a Magic Show
TITLE: Technical Considerations
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: An impromptu tearing off and restoration of a spectator's button

SUBJECT: Routining a Magic Show
TITLE: Acting
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A card is revealed by the inside of a bottle cap previously shown empty

SUBJECT: How to Make People Laugh
TITLE: How To Make People Laugh
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A spectator predicts another spectator's card

SUBJECT: Intimate Magic
TITLE: Christopher's "Double Cross"
DESCRIPTION: Spectator is asked to think of 4 letter words and imagine that those words appear on a blank business card. The spectator says he can see them appearing, but the audience sees just blank business cards.  The spectator holds 4 blank cards and a crayon. Spectator imagines writing each letter of the word he thought of on each of the cards in his hands. When revealed, the letters of his thought of word have been written on his cards.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A safety pin is torn along a handkerchief without harming it.

SUBJECT: Intimate Magic
TITLE: Joe Berg's "Double Cross"
DESCRIPTION: Spectator cuts shuffled deck and looks at top card. Magician spreads an invisible deck out in front of Spectator B and gets Them to name the card.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A ring is placed on a rope under a handkerchief while the ends are in view.

SUBJECT: Intimate Magic
TITLE: Tarbell's Sugar Mark
BOOK_TITLE: Tom Osborne's Ring and Spirit Knot
DESCRIPTION: Spectator opens sugar pack, magician pours it in hand and transforms it to sugar cube. Spectator writes initials on it.  Magician places sugar cube in water and places spectator's hands over water.  Spectator's initials appear on the spectator's hands in different places.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: As above, without using a safety pin.

SUBJECT: Intimate Magic
TITLE: Christopher's Match Book and Coin
DESCRIPTION: Matches are removed from matchbook and matchbook is torn in half.  Halves are rubbed together and quarter appears between them. Halves are then torn in half again.  Spectator rubs 2 halves together and magician rubs 2 other halves.  Quarter appears between magician's halves.  Magician takes halves from spectator and rubs them together to produce another quarter.  1 of the quarters is rolled up and when it is unrolled a quarter is found inside it.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A ring is threaded on a rope, and instantly becomes knotted upon it

SUBJECT: Intimate Magic
TITLE: Christopher's Match Stickler
DESCRIPTION: 1 match is removed from matchbook, burnt, and blown out so head of match is now blackened. Match disappears and reappears inside matchbook.  5 matches are then torn out, 1 match is used to light all the other matches left in matchbook (Spectator is holding the 5 that were torn out). Magician grabs the 5 matches and 1 at a time, places them into the spectator's hand. On the 5th one, spectator closes their hand.  Spectator waves matchbook over their hand. 1 match disappears and reappears inside matchbook with burnt matches.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: The cap of a fountain pen disappears, to reappear back on the pen

SUBJECT: Intimate Magic
TITLE: Audley Walsh Match Routine
DESCRIPTION: 2 matches appears at magician's fingertips.  1 disappears, then reappears.  It disappears again and  reappears. 1 match causes another 1 to jump off magician's hand.  The match disappears then reappears.  Both matches then penetrate each other several times. Match is lit, blown out, Magician makes a gun with his fingers and "shoots" at the match and the head falls off.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Napkin torn into four. Two are torn and rolled, other two are just rolled. Two torn exchange with two untorn pieces. Torn pieces then restore themselves. Finally, all are rolled and restore into the original napkin. Close-up

SUBJECT: Intimate Magic
TITLE: Match Through Safety Pin
DESCRIPTION: Optical illusion to teach kids that some things move faster than the eye and brain can work.  Looks like match goes through a safety pin.  (Science)
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A Crayon is placed in tube and placed behind performer's back. The performer detects the color. This is repeated.

SUBJECT: Intimate Magic
TITLE: Match on Edge
DESCRIPTION: Several spectator are given matches from a matchbook. They are challenged to cause the match to drop on it edge (long edge). None can do it.  Magician grabs one of them and does it first try by "cheating" (slightly bends the match prior to dropping it). Then he grabs another and "adds magic" to it and has that spectator drop it.  When they drop it, the match is seen to have split in half.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Knots instantly appear in a rope

SUBJECT: Intimate Magic
TITLE: Rising and Falling Match
DESCRIPTION: Match torn out of matchbook is lit and dropped in bottle of water.  More water is poured into bottle to "top it off". Match floats in bottle. At magician's command, match sinks to bottom.  At magician's command, match rises.  It does either all at magician's control, even floating in middle of bottle.  (Science)
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: 5 methods to untie a knot in a flourish

SUBJECT: Intimate Magic
TITLE: A Button off the Vest
DESCRIPTION: Circular pendant on necklace being held on by bridal hitch is quickly removed and replaced.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Tying a knot without letting go of the ends Close-up

SUBJECT: Intimate Magic
TITLE: Tavern Trickery
DESCRIPTION: Quarter is borrowed and placed in spectator's hands. Spectator cuts card deck and card they cut to is placed face up on table. Quarter is shaken in hands. Quarter is flipped by spectator to reveal the card is now written on borrowed quarter. Another card is selected. That card is now written on the other side of the quarter.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A rope is threaded through a loop without letting go of the end

SUBJECT: Intimate Magic
TITLE: Christopher's Finger Tip Telepathy
DESCRIPTION: Spectator A selects a card. Spectator B is able to name whether it's red or black, then the suit, then the value. Spectator A confirms all then shows the card.

SUBJECT: Intimate Magic
TITLE: The Phantom Safety Pin
DESCRIPTION: Safety pin stuck in handkerchief is moved without ripping cloth.

SUBJECT: Intimate Magic
TITLE: Ring Rope and Pin, Tom Osbornes Spirit Knot, Ring and the Knot
DESCRIPTION: Rope is laid on table with ends hanging off.  Borrowed ring is laid next to it. Handkerchief is used to cover it. Magician's hands go under handkerchief and ring is placed onto rope (without using ends). It is done again but this time, there is a knot placed in rope and ring is tied into knot.  Magician again ties knot and makes ring penetrate rope and ring ends up tied to knot on rope.

SUBJECT: Intimate Magic
TITLE: A Fountain Pen Nifty
DESCRIPTION: Sharpie cap vanishes from hand and appears back on Sharpie
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Two bills torn, one half of each given to two spectators. Other halves are vanished, and envelope produced. Envelope is opened, and two halves match the ones held by the spectators.

SUBJECT: Intimate Magic
TITLE: Joe Berg's Criss-Cross Paper Napkin
DESCRIPTION: Half of napkin is balled up and covered by spectator. Other half is torn into pieces and balled up then magically switched with spectator's piece.  Then the whole napkin is restored.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Comedy version of Million Dollar Bill Mystery using two Aces of Diamonds.

SUBJECT: Intimate Magic
TITLE: Psychometric Crayons
DESCRIPTION: Magician hands 3 crayons to child. He miscalls the incorrect color each time. 1 crayon is placed into magician's hands, other 2 are placed behind child's back. Magician guesses the correct color in his hand.  This time child places 2 crayons in magician's hand and thinks about the 1 behind his own back.  Magician gets it correct.  Child places all crayons in magician's hands. Magician tries to remember the colors of the crayons behind his back.  Child requests any color crayon and magician instantly pulls it out.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Bill is burned on top of overturned saucer. When saucer is lifted, the restored bill is found.

SUBJECT: Intimate Magic
TITLE: Nifty Knots, Vanishing Knot Flourishes
DESCRIPTION: A knot appears and disappears in a rope, finally ending with 2 knots appearing in the rope.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Bill is placed in envelope; envelope is signed inside and out and sealed. Envelope is cut into two, and so is the bill, as demonstrated when two half dollars are poured from the envelope.

SUBJECT: Intimate Magic
TITLE: G.W. Hunter's Puzzle Knot
DESCRIPTION: Magician challenges child to attempt to tie a knot in a rope without letting go of the ends. After child can't do it, Magician does it several times including with the child holding 1 end, then both ends.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Vanished bill found inside Life Savers candy pack. Two versions.

SUBJECT: Intimate Magic
TITLE: Bachelor's Needle
DESCRIPTION: Rope penetrates itself like threading the eye of a needle.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Dollar is borrowed and torn in two. Magician gives spectator half, which turns out to be a half dollar coin. Magician takes half dollar back and restores the bill.

SUBJECT: Conjuring with Currency
TITLE: John Scarne's Bill Change
DESCRIPTION: $1 turns into $100.  $1 is now found in change purse.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A dollar bill is used to strike and break a pencil, but the dollar breaks instead and drops change on the floor. Finally, another dollar is tried using a stunt and breaks the pencil.

SUBJECT: Conjuring with Currency
TITLE: Grant's Slow Motion Bill Transposition
DESCRIPTION: Spectator folds their $1 as magician folds their $20. Magician takes both. Both go in spectator's hand and magician pulls out $1. $1 turns into $20.  When spectator opens his hand, he is holding $1.
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A bill is shown and folded cleanly. When unfolded, the bill has turned upside down.

SUBJECT: Conjuring with Currency
TITLE: Grant's "Million Dollar" Bill Mystery
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A dollar bill is cut into four, and four full dollars are produced, one from each piece.

SUBJECT: Conjuring with Currency
TITLE: The Persnickety Pinochle Player
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Similar to One to Four using Newspaper

SUBJECT: Conjuring with Currency
TITLE: Novel Burned and Restored Bill
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: How to quickly memorize dollar serial number for a quick stunt

SUBJECT: Conjuring with Currency
TITLE: Half and Half
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A stunt. New bills are 'torn' from a checkbook style cover.

SUBJECT: Conjuring with Currency
TITLE: The Life Saver
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Another stunt. Bills are joined at the ends in a 'roll' of bills.

SUBJECT: Conjuring with Currency
TITLE: A Dollar Makes a "Break" & The Topsy-Turvy Bill

SUBJECT: Conjuring with Currency
TITLE: Berland's One to Four
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Stack of 4 coins opens between the fingers

SUBJECT: Conjuring with Currency
TITLE: Instant Number Memorization
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: dime, nickle, quarter, and half rapidly produced

SUBJECT: Conjuring with Currency
TITLE: A Roll of Bills
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Dime placed on back of magician's hand and covered with a Half Dollar. Half is removed and dime has vanished, to be found inside the hand. Only one dime and half used.

SUBJECT: Modern Coin Effects
TITLE: Manuel's Coin Star
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Copper/Silver tranposition using one copper and one silver

SUBJECT: Modern Coin Effects
TITLE: The Four Coin Flourish
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Silver dollar and dime transform repeatedly at the fingertips

SUBJECT: Modern Coin Effects
TITLE: Al Zink's Coin Production
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: variation of above used as coin change

SUBJECT: Modern Coin Effects
TITLE: Combo Coin Routine
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Impromptu 2 coin routine. Can be combined with Back and Forth or used alone. Uses sleeving and French Drop. With rhyming patter.

SUBJECT: Modern Coin Effects
TITLE: Paul Morris' Ubiquitous Coin & Back and Forth
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A continuation of Paul Morris' Ubiquitous Coin, or can be used alone.

SUBJECT: Modern Coin Effects
TITLE: French "Pill Box" Coin Mystery
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Three coins vanish from a pill box and wind up inside a bag in a box in another box all sealed by rubber bands.

SUBJECT: Modern Coin Effects
TITLE: Coins in a Loaf of Bread
BOOK_TITLE: Coins in a Loaf of Bread
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Similar to French Pill Box Coin Mystery.

SUBJECT: Modern Coin Effects
TITLE: Okito Coin Box
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Three methods of performing a vanishing coin

SUBJECT: Modern Coin Effects
TITLE: Dime Delusion
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: Dime is tossed into two whisky glasses held mouth to mouth

SUBJECT: Modern Coin Effects
TITLE: Tom Osborne's Five Coin Routine
BOOK_DESCRIPTION: A mini-Miser's Dream routine, uses bottomless glass

SUBJECT: Modern Coin Effects
TITLE: The "Throw-Away" Coin Vanish

DESCRIPTION: A convincing penetration through the neck that can be performed with a scarf, ribbon, rope, or tie. Improved with a little twist.

SUBJECT: Modern Stage Magic
TITLE: Berland's Tray Servante
DESCRIPTION: An easy to make utility device that turns any tray into a versatile, secret servante.

SUBJECT: Modern Stage Magic
TITLE: Judge Wethered's Black Art Tray
DESCRIPTION: A utility table that allows you to make just about anything appear or vanish without sleight-of-hand. Comes complete with a cups and balls beer pong routine.

SUBJECT: Modern Stage Magic
TITLE: The Hindu Turban Mystery
DESCRIPTION: The classic cut-and-restored rope gets a stage-size upgrade to play to a much bigger crowd.

SUBJECT: Modern Stage Magic
TITLE: Don Greenwood's Lighted Cigarette Routine
DESCRIPTION: A full cigarette manipulation routine with a big ending. You'll learn how to make the craziest smoking jacket you have ever seen.

SUBJECT: Modern Stage Magic
TITLE: Jack Chanin's Cigarette Routine
DESCRIPTION: The cigarettes here are replaced with french fries to have a little fun with some fast food, finally ending up with a fresh vegetable snack.

SUBJECT: Modern Stage Magic
TITLE: George Sands' Cigarette Production
DESCRIPTION: You'll learn all about the challenges of shooting magic underwater as a somewhat standard cigarette routine gets a completely surreal re-working.

SUBJECT: Modern Stage Magic
TITLE: Jimmy Herpick's Cigarette Routine
DESCRIPTION: The cigarettes here are replaced with crayons to show you how the same techniques work just as well, including the final production of a jumbo sharpie

SUBJECT: Modern Stage Magic
TITLE: George Sands' "Phantom" Cigarette
DESCRIPTION: You'll learn how to roll an invisible cigarette and make it impossibly appear in front of your audience.

SUBJECT: Modern Stage Magic
TITLE: David Tobias Bamberg's Coin in Ball of Wool
DESCRIPTION: A signed coin vanishes and ends up inside the center of a ball of yarn.

SUBJECT: Modern Stage Magic
TITLE: David Tobias Bamberg's Ring in Ball of Wool
DESCRIPTION: A borrowed ring vanishes and ends up inside the center of a ball of yarn.

SUBJECT: Modern Stage Magic
TITLE: Ed Reno's Knife through the Arm
DESCRIPTION: You will learn how to plunge a pair of scissors right through your palm.

SUBJECT: Stage Productions
TITLE: UF Grant's Carton Production
DESCRIPTION: You will learn how to make an innocent-looking cardboard box that can be shown completely empty, yet allows you to produce just about anything you want.

SUBJECT: Stage Productions
TITLE: The Square and Circle Production
DESCRIPTION: Two routines using the versatile Square and Circle production box. Produce anything you want on stage. When you really want to go big on a budget, you can't do much better than this.

SUBJECT: Stage Productions
TITLE: Vincent Malmstrom's Organ Pipe Routine
DESCRIPTION: Three tubes are shown empty yet produce a bountiful banquet of food and beverages sure to impress all your guests.

SUBJECT: Stage Productions

DESCRIPTION: A brand new design for the infamous Doll House illusion allowing the entire interior to be displayed.

SUBJECT: Stage Productions
TITLE: Christopher's Slot Machine Illusion
DESCRIPTION: Produce a Las Vegas Showgirl from an antique slot machine.
